b'[<p><i><b>UFC on FX: Belfort vs. Rockhold</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC on FX 8</b></i>) was a mixed martial arts event held on May 18, 2013, at the <a href="/wiki/Arena_Jaragu%C3%A1" title="Arena Jaragu\xc3\xa1">Arena Jaragu\xc3\xa1</a> in <a href="/wiki/Jaragu%C3%A1_do_Sul" title="Jaragu\xc3\xa1 do Sul">Jaragu\xc3\xa1 do Sul</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FX8_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-FX8-3">[3]</a></sup>  The event was broadcast live on <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/FUEL_TV" title="FUEL TV">FUEL TV</a> and <a href="/wiki/FX_(TV_channel)" title="FX (TV channel)">FX</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was headlined by a middleweight bout between perennial multi-divisional contender <a href="/wiki/Vitor_Belfort" title="Vitor Belfort">Vitor Belfort</a> and the final <a href="/wiki/List_of_Strikeforce_champions" title="List of Strikeforce champions">Strikeforce Middleweight Champion</a> and promotional newcomer and future UFC Middleweight Champion <a href="/wiki/Luke_Rockhold" title="Luke Rockhold">Luke Rockhold</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-FX8_3-1"><a href="#cite_note-FX8-3">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Manvel_Gamburyan" title="Manvel Gamburyan">Manvel Gamburyan</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Hacran_Dias" title="Hacran Dias">Hacran Dias</a> at the event.  However, Gamburyan was forced to pull out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Nik_Lentz" title="Nik Lentz">Nik Lentz</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-LentzIn_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-LentzIn-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Marcos_Vinicius_(fighter)" title="Marcos Vinicius (fighter)">Marcos Vin\xc3\xadcius</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Iuri_Alc%C3%A2ntara" title="Iuri Alc\xc3\xa2ntara">Iuri Alc\xc3\xa2ntara</a> at the event. However, Vinicius was forced out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Iliarde_Santos" title="Iliarde Santos">Iliarde Santos</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-5"><a href="#cite_note-5">[5]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-SantosIn_6-0"><a href="#cite_note-SantosIn-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Cezar_Ferreira" title="Cezar Ferreira">Cezar Ferreira</a> was originally scheduled to face <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/CB_Dollaway" title="CB Dollaway">CB Dollaway</a>.  However, on April 1, it was revealed that Dollaway had to withdraw from the bout due to injury and he was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Chris_Camozzi" title="Chris Camozzi">Chris Camozzi</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-7"><a href="#cite_note-7">[7]</a></sup> Then on April 7, it was confirmed that Ferreira had pulled out of the fight as well, citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Rafael_Natal" title="Rafael Natal">Rafael Natal</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[8]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Costas_Philippou" title="Costas Philippou">Costas Philippou</a> had to withdraw from his fight against <a href="/wiki/Ronaldo_Souza" title="Ronaldo Souza">Ronaldo Souza</a>, after suffering a cut above his eye, and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Chris_Camozzi" title="Chris Camozzi">Chris Camozzi</a>.  Camozzi\'s scheduled opponent <a href="/wiki/Rafael_Natal" title="Rafael Natal">Rafael Natal</a> instead faced promotional newcomer <a href="/wiki/Jo%C3%A3o_Zeferino" title="Jo\xc3\xa3o Zeferino">Jo\xc3\xa3o Zeferino</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-9"><a href="#cite_note-9">[9]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PhilippouOut_10-0"><a href="#cite_note-PhilippouOut-10">[10]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Paulo_Thiago" title="Paulo Thiago">Paulo Thiago</a> was originally expected to face <a href="/wiki/Lance_Benoist" title="Lance Benoist">Lance Benoist</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-11"><a href="#cite_note-11">[11]</a></sup> However, on April 20, it was announced that Benoist had to pull out of the bout due to an injury and was replaced by UFC newcomer <a href="/wiki/Michel_Prazeres" title="Michel Prazeres">Michel Prazeres</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-BenoistOut_12-0"><a href="#cite_note-BenoistOut-12">[12]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-14"><a href="#cite_note-14">[13]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-15"><a href="#cite_note-15">[14]</a></sup>\n</p>]'